.H 2 "unsplit"
The
.I unsplit
function is used to glue strings together,
using the specified glue.
The first argument is the text to go between
each of the second and subsequent arguments.
.H 3 "Example"
.TS
center,tab(;);
l l.
Expression;Result
_
[unsplit ":" one two three];"one:two:three"
[unsplit " " four five six];"four five six"
.TE
The quotes are necessary to isolate characters such as colon and space
which cook would normally treat differently.
.H 3 "See Also"
catenate,
prepost,
split
